extends layout

block pageTitle
  title Privacy Policy — Hedge Wears

block metaDesc
  meta(name='description' content='Learn how Hedge Wears collects, uses, and protects your personal data.')

block content

  //- ─── PAGE HERO ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  section.page-hero.section
    .container
      .page-hero-inner.page-hero-inner--centered
        span.section-eyebrow Legal
        h1.page-hero-title Privacy Policy
        p.page-hero-subtitle Last updated: January 2025

  //- ─── CONTENT ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  section.legal-page.section
    .container
      .legal-content

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 1. Information We Collect
          p We collect information you provide directly when you create an account, make a purchase, or contact us. This includes your name, email address, delivery address, and payment details (processed securely through Paystack — we do not store card numbers).
          p We also collect information automatically when you use the app or website, including device type, operating system, IP address, browsing behaviour, and crash logs. This data helps us improve the platform and diagnose technical issues.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 2. How We Use Your Information
          p We use your information to:
          ul
            li Process and fulfil your orders and send order confirmations and updates.
            li Credit and track your HedgeCoin (HGC) balance and transaction history.
            li Send you push notifications about your orders and, if you have opted in, promotions and new arrivals.
            li Improve the platform by analysing usage patterns and diagnosing problems.
            li Respond to your support enquiries and resolve disputes.
            li Comply with legal obligations and prevent fraudulent activity.
          p We do not sell your personal data to third parties.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 3. Data Sharing
          p We share data only where necessary to operate the service:
          ul
            li
              strong Sellers:
              |  When you place an order, your name, delivery address, and order details are shared with the relevant seller so they can fulfil your order.
            li
              strong Payment processor (Paystack):
              |  Your payment information is passed to Paystack for secure transaction processing. Paystack's privacy policy governs how they handle this data.
            li
              strong Service providers:
              |  We use third-party services for cloud hosting, push notifications (Firebase), and analytics. These providers process data on our behalf and are bound by data processing agreements.
            li
              strong Legal requirements:
              |  We may disclose data if required by law, court order, or to protect the rights and safety of our users and the public.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 4. Data Retention
          p We retain your account data for as long as your account is active. If you delete your account, we will delete your personal data within 30 days, except where we are required to retain it by law (for example, transaction records for tax purposes).
          p Aggregated and anonymised usage analytics may be retained indefinitely as they cannot be used to identify you.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 5. Your Rights
          p Depending on your location, you may have the right to:
          ul
            li Access the personal data we hold about you.
            li Request correction of inaccurate data.
            li Request deletion of your account and associated data.
            li Object to or restrict certain types of processing.
            li Receive a copy of your data in a portable format.
          p To exercise any of these rights, email us at
            a.link(href='mailto:hello@hedgewears.com')  hello@hedgewears.com
            |  with the subject line "Privacy Request." We will respond within 30 days.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 6. Cookies &amp; Tracking
          p The Hedge Wears website uses cookies to maintain your session and remember your preferences. We use analytics cookies (anonymised) to understand how pages are used. You can disable cookies in your browser settings, though this may affect some functionality.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 7. Security
          p We take reasonable technical and organisational measures to protect your data from unauthorised access, loss, or disclosure. However, no system is completely secure and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 8. Children
          p Hedge Wears is not directed at children under 16. We do not knowingly collect data from children. If you believe a child has provided us with data, please contact us and we will delete it promptly.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 9. Changes to This Policy
          p We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of significant changes by email or via an in-app notification. Continued use of Hedge Wears after changes are published constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 10. Contact
          p For privacy-related questions or requests, contact us at:
          p
            a.link(href='mailto:hello@hedgewears.com') hello@hedgewears.com
          p Hedge Wears, London, United Kingdom.
